	heroObjectPosition={`center center`}
	directAnswerHtml={`<strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">If you're a teacher, the Father's Heart Bible™ is for you.</strong> You carry more than anyone sees — the late nights grading, the emotional labor of caring for kids who aren't your own, the quiet ache of feeling undervalued and unseen. The <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Father's Heart Bible™</a> is a fresh English translation you can read and <em>listen to</em> free on your phone — and it reveals God as a <em>Father</em> from beginning to end. Whether you searched "bible verses for teachers," "encouragement for teachers," or "scripture for educators" — the answer starts in one place: you were never meant to pour from an empty cup. Before you give to anyone else, you are a beloved child your Father wants to fill first.`}
	keyTakeaway={`You are not valued because of your test scores, your workload, or how much you give away. You are the Father's beloved child — fathered first, filled first — so you can teach from overflow instead of running on empty.`}
	painsHeading={`The weight teachers carry`}
	painsIntroHtml={`If you feel burned out, exhausted, or like you're giving far more than you ever get back, you are not weak and you are not alone. A whole profession is carrying the same weight — and the numbers say it out loud.`}
	painStats={[
		{ value: `52%`, label: `of teachers reported feeling burned out at work "always" or "very often" — K-12 workers have the highest burnout rate of any U.S. industry (Gallup, 2022)` },
