	painsBodyHtml={`<p>Behind every statistic is a real teacher — maybe you. The cup that empties faster than anyone refills it. The evenings and weekends swallowed by grading and prep. The students you carry home in your heart, the parents to answer, the budget that never stretches far enough, the sense that the whole world leans on you while few stop to ask how you are.</p><p>None of this means you're failing. It means you're human, doing one of the most poured-out jobs there is in a world that rarely pours back. There is a Father who sees the giver behind the gift — who wants to fill you first, so the well you draw from never has to run dry.</p>`}
	painsSources={[
		{ label: `Gallup — K-12 Workers Have Highest Burnout Rate in U.S.`, url: `https://news.gallup.com/poll/393500/workers-highest-burnout-rate.aspx` },
		{ label: `RAND — State of the American Teacher Survey 2024`, url: `https://www.rand.org/pubs/research_reports/RRA1108-12.html` },
		{ label: `NEA — Educator Pay Data 2024`, url: `https://www.nea.org/resource-library/educator-pay-data-2024` },
	]}
	aFatherHeading={`A Father for teachers`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>Here's what almost no one tells you in the middle of a hard school year: the answer to the burnout isn't a better system, a thicker skin, or simply giving even more of yourself. The answer is a <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong> — a perfect, holy Father who already loves you, today, before you grade a single paper.</p><p>You were not made to be an endless well that fills itself. You were made to be filled. And the One who made you doesn't measure you by your students' scores, your hours, or how much you sacrifice. He calls you His beloved child — not the tireless teacher version, not the one who never breaks — but <em>you</em>, weary and worn and worthy of love.</p><p>So before you are an educator, a mentor, a manager of thirty small lives, a name on a classroom door — you are His. Your heavenly Father wants to be the One who pours into you first, the steady voice that says: I see how much you give, I'm proud of you, and you don't have to be empty for Me to love you. Come and be filled.</p>`}
