	voiceHeading={`Bible verses for teachers: the Father's voice`}
	voiceIntroHtml={`Nine Bible verses for teachers in the Father's Heart Bible™ — each one a word from your perfect Father, straight to the weariness you're carrying. Tap any reference to read and listen free.`}
	verses={[
		{ ref: `Matthew 11:28-30`, slug: `matthew`, ch: 11, text: `Come to Me, all who are weary and heavy-laden, and I will give you rest; take My yoke upon you and learn from Me, for I am gentle, and you will find rest for your soul.`, note: `When you're running on empty by Tuesday, your Father isn't asking for more — He's offering you rest.` },
		{ ref: `Isaiah 40:31`, slug: `isaiah`, ch: 40, text: `But those who wait on your Father will renew their strength; they will rise on wings like eagles, run and not grow weary, walk and not faint.`, note: `The strength you've spent isn't gone for good — your Father renews what teaching drains out of you.` },
		{ ref: `Galatians 6:9`, slug: `galatians`, ch: 6, text: `Let us not grow weary in doing good, for in due season you will reap a harvest, if you do not give up.`, note: `The seeds you plant in students you may never see bloom — but your Father promises the harvest is coming.` },
		{ ref: `2 Corinthians 4:16`, slug: `2-corinthians`, ch: 4, text: `So do not lose heart; though your outer self is wearing down, your inner self is being renewed by your Father day by day.`, note: `Even on the days the job wears you thin, your Father is quietly renewing you from the inside out.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 23:1-3`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 23, text: `Your Father is your shepherd; you shall not be in want. He makes you lie down in green pastures, He leads you beside still waters, He restores your soul.`, note: `When you have nothing left to give, your Father makes you rest and restores the soul you keep pouring out.` },
		{ ref: `Colossians 3:23-24`, slug: `colossians`, ch: 3, text: `Whatever you do, work at it with all your heart, as for your Father and not for people, knowing that from Him you will receive your reward.`, note: `Even when no one notices the hours you give, your Father sees every one — and He is the One who rewards you.` },
		{ ref: `Philippians 4:6-7`, slug: `philippians`, ch: 4, text: `Do not be anxious about anything, but in everything, by prayer, bring your requests to your Father — and His peace, beyond all understanding, will guard your heart and mind.`, note: `Hand Him the worry over that student, that meeting, that long list — and let His peace stand guard instead.` },
		{ ref: `Isaiah 43:1`, slug: `isaiah`, ch: 43, text: `Fear not, for I have redeemed you; I have called you by name — you are Mine, says your Father.`, note: `You're not just a number on a staff list to Him. Your Father knows your name and calls you His own.` },
		{ ref: `Zephaniah 3:17`, slug: `zephaniah`, ch: 3, text: `Your Father is in your midst, a mighty one who will save; He will rejoice over you with gladness and quiet you with His love; He will sing over you.`, note: `After a day of pouring out, picture this: your Father delights in you and quiets your tired heart with His love.` },
