	voicesCreditHtml={`Photos via <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Wikimedia Commons</a> &mdash; George MacDonald, Charles Spurgeon, and Andrew Murray (all public domain).`}
	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>You might not feel different the first time you read it. That's okay. The Father's love isn't a hype feeling — it's a foundation, and foundations get built quietly, one day at a time. Every verse you take in is your Father refilling something in you that the school year keeps draining out.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What your Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"I see how much you give. I see the early mornings and the late nights, the student you can't stop praying for, the way you keep showing up even when your cup is empty and no one refills it. And I want you to hear Me over all of it: you are Mine, and I love you right now — not the tireless teacher, not the one who never breaks. You.</p><p>You don't have to earn My love by giving more, and you can't lose it by needing rest. I made you on purpose, and I delight in you apart from anything you produce. When you are weary and worn thin, come to Me — I'll restore your soul and renew your strength, and I'll quiet your tired heart with My love. You were never meant to pour from an empty cup. Let Me fill you first. I'm your Father, I'm proud of you, and nothing in this world can change that."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for teachers`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we thank You and praise You for these teachers — every educator carrying far more than anyone sees. Let them hear Your whisper above the noise — the deadlines, the demands, the weight of caring for so many. Let them encounter Your love — not as one more duty, but as a Father's delight — and know they are Your beloved, apart from their results, their workload, or anyone's approval.</p><p>Give them grace to receive from You before they pour out for everyone else. Father, fill the empty cup, restore the weary soul, and renew the strength this work keeps draining. I pray Your protection over them — from burnout and bitterness, from exhaustion and despair, from the lie that they must run on empty to be enough.</p><p>Provide for them where they feel undervalued and unseen, and let them know that You see every unnoticed hour and call it precious. Let them rest in green pastures and beside still waters, and let them teach from the overflow of being loved by You. And may they wake up every single day knowing they are loved by their heavenly Father.</p><p>In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
