	faqs={[
		{ question: `What are good Bible verses for teachers?`, answer: `Matthew 11:28-30 (come to Me, all who are weary, and I will give you rest), Isaiah 40:31 (those who wait on the Lord renew their strength), Galatians 6:9 (do not grow weary in doing good), 2 Corinthians 4:16 (do not lose heart — you are renewed day by day), Psalm 23 (He restores my soul), Colossians 3:23-24 (work as for the Lord, who rewards you), and Philippians 4:6-7 (do not be anxious) all speak straight to what teachers carry. Read and hear them free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about teacher burnout?`, answer: `Scripture takes your exhaustion seriously and offers a real place to bring it. Matthew 11:28-30 invites the weary and heavy-laden to come and find rest for their souls, and Isaiah 40:31 promises that those who wait on God renew their strength. The Father's Heart Bible™ reveals God as a Father who wants to fill you first instead of asking you to give more — read those passages free, with audio, at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Is there a free Bible with audio for teachers and educators?`, answer: `Yes. The Father's Heart Bible™ is free to read and listen to online — no account, no purchase, no app. Open fathersheartbible.com/read on your phone and read or hear any book — perfect for listening on the commute, during your prep period, or in the quiet after the last student leaves.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about feeling undervalued or unseen at work?`, answer: `The Bible reframes who your work is really for. Colossians 3:23-24 says to work with all your heart as for the Lord and not for people, because He is the One who sees and rewards you. Galatians 6:9 promises that the good you do — even unnoticed — will reap a harvest in due season. In the Father's Heart Bible™ you meet God as a Father who sees every unseen hour. Read these free at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What are good scripture verses for educators who are exhausted?`, answer: `Psalm 23 (He makes me lie down in green pastures, He restores my soul), 2 Corinthians 4:16 (though the outer self wears down, the inner self is renewed day by day), and Isaiah 40:31 (renew their strength, run and not be weary) speak directly to exhaustion. The Father's Heart Bible™ presents these as words from a Father who wants to restore you, not drain you — read free with audio at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What makes the Father's Heart Bible™ different for teachers?`, answer: `It's the first English translation to reveal God as Father wherever Scripture reveals Him as Father — so instead of reading one more voice asking you to give more, you meet the One who wants to fill you first. For a teacher pouring out all day, that reframes everything: you come to the Bible as a loved child being filled, not a giver being asked for more.` },
		{ question: `How can I start reading the Bible as a busy teacher?`, answer: `Start small and start free. Open fathersheartbible.com/read, pick a short book or a Psalm, and listen to the audio while you commute or grade. Try a verse a day — Matthew 11, Psalm 23, or Isaiah 40 are great places to begin. Our how-to-pray guide and verses-by-topic pages can help you find words for whatever you're facing right now.` },
